                          बाल अपराध                  





                     बाल अपराध का अर्थ

          बाल अपराधी को दो वर्गों में रखा गया है
          1- प्रौढ़ या युवा अपराधी (15-18) 

          2- बाल अपराधी (15 से कम) 


           " 15 वर्ष के कम आयु के बालक को 
           बाल अपराधी कहते हैं "
   
          जब बच्चों का नटखटपन सीमा लांघकर
            सामाजिक मान्यताओं को भंग करने
         लगता है या कानून का उल्लंघन करने 
          लगता है तो उसे बाल अपराध कहते हैं



   
                बाल अपराधी की परिभाषा

          1 - बर्ट के अनुसार- 
         " हम उस बालक को अपराधी समझेंगे
         जिसकी समाज-विरोधी प्रवृत्तियाँ इतनी
           बढ़ जाती है कि प्रशासन को उसके 
          विरूद्ध कोई न कोई कार्यवाही करनी
          पडती है "


         2- मात्र के अनुसार -
          " बाल अपराधी वह व्यक्ति हैं, जो 
          जानबूझकर चेतन रूप से उस समाज  
           की रूढ़ियों उपेक्षा करता है जिससे 
          उसका सम्बन्ध हैं " 





                   बाल अपराध के प्रकार

          चोरी करना, झूठ बोलना, जुआ खेलना
           धूम्रपान और मघपान,दुसरो को पीड़ा
          करना, विघालय से भाग जाना
          तोड़ फोड़ करना तथा स्कूल की वस्तुएं
          नष्ट करना
          अश्लील बातें बकना व दिवारों पर गन्दी
           बातें लिखना   
          राह चलती लड़कियों को छेड़ना
          निर्लज्ज प्रदर्शन तथा नंगापन
          रेलवे लाइन पर निरूद्देय घूमना
          सडकों पर अकारण आवारागर्दी करना
          समलैंगिक या भिन्न लिंग मैथुन करना
       




               बाल अपराध के प्रमुख कारण 

            1- व्यक्तित्व सम्बन्धी कारण
            2- जैवकीय व शारीरिक कारण

title: Cold Case at Carlton's Canyon - Rita Herron 1 (AudioBook)
description:
Two officers' badges—and hearts—are on the line in Rita Herron's Cold Case at Carlton's Canyon

Sergeant Justin Thorpe has dedicated his life to justice and won't stop until he finds the vicious serial killer who has already claimed ten innocent lives. He works solo—until he joins forces with Sheriff Amanda Blair. The Texas Ranger can't let his desire for his coworker keep him from his mission, especially when Amanda's life is threatened.

Ten girls have vanished—one for every year since Amanda graduated from Canyon High. And as she tries to fight her attraction to a man as independent as she is, a trap is being laid to make Amanda the final victim in a killer's terrifying endgame….

title: Crime Patrol - क्राइम पेट्रोल सतर्क - Ep 829 - Murder At Midnight - 14th July, 2017
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SetIndia Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Dial 100 - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupzBi22rTZgQbnRMWVCrUEvP

Episode 829:
---------------------
Durga, a middle-aged woman, is stabbed to death at midnight. After committing the crime, the assailant disappears into the darkness. Her neighbours hear her cries and rush to her aid but it is too late as Durga bleeds to death. The police begin investigation into the murder and suspect that Satish is the murderer. However, the relationship between Durga and Satish was a complicated one as Durga treated Satish as her son. If so, why did Satish take such an extreme step and murder Durga? Watch this episode to find out. 

Crime Patrol:
---------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Agression d'un proche de Brigitte Macron : la réaction d'Emmanuel Macron
description:

title: Arrest made in 1996 Bronx cold case
description:
Police have made an arrest in a cold case murder dating back more than 25 years.

The NYPD arrested 66-year-old Gregory Fleetwood in connection with the 1996 murder of Jasmine Porter in the Bronx.

Porter, who was 36, was found dead inside her home on Davidson Avenue.

Police said she had bruises on her neck.

title: समझौता | Crime Patrol | Viewer's Choice
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SET India Channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1

Click to watch all the special episodes of Crime Patrol:
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupzmzTUmYFZJe4UhLkm23APh

Relive the best episodes of your favorite crime-thriller show, Crime Patrol.  

About the show:
--------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:

Click here to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Dastak: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0y08jtgaKIXQP1i0ziNFbdM5MSMigy1g

Crime series that will give you literal spine chills and cases turning out to be unbelievably true. From attacking innocents to bludgeoning them. Every case will ignite a fire, will put one in agony, and hunger for justice will prevail. 

In today's episode of Crime Patrol we see a familial problem where a girl is supposed to get married and is annoyed with her fiance regarding his secret from his past. And then suddenly, she goes missing. Stay tuned to find out what turns this story takes. 
 
Show Name: Crime Patrol
Host: Sanjeev Tyagi
Producers: Prem Krishen Malhotra, Sunil Mehta, Vipul D. Shah, Anirban Bhattacharyya

#crimepatrol #क्राइमपेट्रोल #livcrime

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:
This week on Murder With Friends Grace is joined by film critics Dave White and Alonso Duralde to discuss the mythos surrounding American serial killer, H.H. Holmes and his purported "Murder Castle". Part 3 details Holmes' confession and breaks down the factors that contributed to his story becoming lore.

Hosted by Grace Baldridge, each week friends join to discuss real life murders from throughout history - from serial killers to massacres and assassinations: This is true crime unfiltered.

title: City Crime | Crime Patrol | Aim-Part 2 | Jodhpur | Full Episode
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SET India Channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1

Watch special episodes of Crime Patrol handpicked from different corners of India

About the show Crime Patrol:
------------------------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Sikhs, Spies and Murder: Investigating India’s alleged hit on foreign soil | Foreign Correspondent
description:
When Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau stood up and accused India of being behind the killing of a Sikh activist on Canadian soil last year the world took notice. To have a head of state call out another country for effectively a state sponsored assassination was eye popping. Then, months later, US authorities said an Indian agent was involved in a murder attempt on an American Sikh in New York. Now Foreign Correspondent can reveal Australian authorities are also speaking to the Sikh community here.  

This week South Asia Correspondent Avani Dias travels to Punjab where tensions are high and the authorities are watching. This is the Sikh homeland where a banned separatist movement is fighting to create its own independent nation of Khalistan. Avani visits the family home of the man murdered in Canada Hardeep Singh Nijjar. and learns of unusual activity in the lead up to his killing. She also gains rare access to the movement's leaders, viewed as extremists by Indian officials, who are in no doubt the Modi government is targeting Sikh separatists around the world including Australia. 

Subscribe: https://ab.co/3yqPOZ5

title: Oldest Cold Case FINALLY Solved In 2023 Mary Agnes Moroney
description:
After almost a century, the oldest cold case on record has finally been solved with the help of forensic science and extensive investigations. Mary Agnes Moroney, a victim of a heinous crime, can now rest in peace, as her case is closed and justice is served. This historical crime investigation utilized criminal profiling, homicide detectives, and DNA evidence to bring closure to the case. The breakthrough in the cold case, through forensic evidence analysis, is a significant achievement in the criminal justice system and has solved one of the greatest unsolved mysteries in true crime history. The work of the cold case unit and the reopening of the case is a testament to the importance of crime solving and case closure.

title: وثائقي تحقيقات جرائم القتل.. جريمة لم تحدث لها مثيل في هذه البلدة الصغيرة خلال أكثر من 40 عامًا!!
description:
مرحبًا بكم في وثائقي مذهل ومليء بالغموض، حيث نلقي الضوء على جريمة لم تحدث لها مثيل في بلدة صغيرة تشهد أحداثاً لأول مرة خلال أكثر من 40 عامًا! إنها القصة التي هزت البلدة وأثارت الاستغراب والذهول في نفس الوقت.

في هذا الوثائقي، سنكشف لكم تفاصيل الحادثة الغامضة ونستعرض الأدلة والشهادات التي تكشف عن أبعاد هذه الجريمة الصادمة. سنسلط الضوء على عمليات التحقيق والتحليل التي أجريت لمحاولة فهم ما حدث وتحديد هوية المتورطين فيها.


استعدوا لمشاهدة لقطات حصرية ومثيرة ولسماع شهادات من الشهود والمحققين، وسنأخذكم في رحلة مشوقة لاستكشاف تفاصيل هذه الجريمة الفريدة التي لا تصدقها عقول.
انضموا إلينا في هذه الرحلة المثيرة، واستعدوا للانغماس في عالم الجريمة والتحقيق، حيث ستكشف لكم الحقائق الصادمة والغموض الذي يحيط بالقضية.

title: Crime Patrol - क्राइम पेट्रोल सतर्क - Case 7 / 2017 - Episode 760 - 21st January, 2017
description:
Subscribe to setindia channel for daily entertainment dose
https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Satark  -  https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c
In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a multiple murder case. Sangita is a widow who stays along with her daughter Aarti. Sangita's niece Vaishali and nephew Rohit often stay in her house during nights. Once, on a winter morning, the police find Sangita, Aarti, Vaishali and Rohit's dead bodies in the house. While investigating, the police find out that Sangita had an affair with an anonymous person. Want to know more? Then stay tuned in and find out here.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, “It should not have happened”.Would knowing the “Why” behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?“I don’t like the way he looks at me”, “I don’t like the way he/she is behaving”, “I think he/she is out of his/her mind”, “I think he/she has gone crazy”. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: A Husband's Heartbreaking Betrayal Destroys Two Women's Lives! | Crime Patrol | Inspector Series
description:
A couple meets after a long time as they were missing each other. The man had cooked something special for the lady which he learned through a video in which a woman teaches to cook. The next day, the man wakes up and starts to walk and finds the lady lying on the floor in critical condition. Watch the full episode to know more.

Show Name: Crime Patrol
Host: Divyanka Tripathi Dahiya
Producers: Prem Krishen Malhotra, Sunil Mehta, Vipul D. Shah, Anirban Bhattacharyya

#crimepatrol #क्राइमपेट्रोल #setindia 

Click here to Subscribe to SET India: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCpEhnqL0y41EpW2TvWAHD7Q?sub_confirmation=1

About Crime Patrol :
-----------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

description:
#باب_الحارة

باب الحارة الجزء الثالث
مسلسل سوري من إخراج بسام الملا وتأليف مروان قاووق. وقد شهد بعض التغيير في مسار الأحداث والشخصيات، فقد استبعد الفنان عباس النوري الذي قام بدور أبي عصام في جزئيه الأول والثاني، واستبدال ديمة قندلفت وإيمان عبد العزيز وتاج حيدر وليلى سمور وقيس الشيخ نجيب بكل من إمارات رزق وعزة البحرة ودانة جبر وشكران مرتجى وجهاد عبدو على التوالي. فضلاً عن مشاركة نجوم المسلسل في جزئيه الأول والثاني وهم سامر المصري وصباح الجزائري وميلاد يوسف ووائل شرف وغيرهم. أضيفت في هذا الجزء شخصيات جديدة مثل أبو عرب (أيمن رضا) وحمدي (أندريه سكاف) والمختار أبو صياح (صالح الحايك) وأبو علي (مؤيد الملا) وغيرهم.

title: Consentement et agression sexuelle
description:
😍 ABONNEZ-VOUS POUR RECEVOIR NOS PROCHAINES VIDÉOS EN EXCLUSIVITÉ 👍🏽

Pour plus d'information, rendez-vous sur https://violences-sexuelles.info/
Une initiative du CRIAVS Île-de-France (https://criavs.fr) / Hôpitaux de Saint-Maurice, en partenariat avec l'Association Une Vie (https://1vie.org)

+++
Facebook : https://www.facebook.com/infoviolencesex/
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/violences_sexuelles/
Twitter : https://twitter.com/violences_sex
+++

On a tous connu ce moment où on se demande si on a vraiment envie de faire l'amour...
Et l'autre, est-ce qu'il se pose la question ? Et est-ce qu'il en a vraiment envie ?
Et qu'est-ce que c'est dire oui ? À quoi est-ce que je dis oui, d'ailleurs ? Et comment dire non ? Et comment dire stop ?
Et si j'ai pas dit non, est-ce que c'est un viol ?

Le consentement à une relation sexuelle, ça pose un tas de questions. Et autant vous prévenir tout de suite, les réponses sont pas si claires que ça. Mais avec ce site, on va essayer d'y répondre, de vous donner des outils, et de vous aider à y voir plus clair.

Cette histoire de consentement à une relation sexuelle, elle date pas d'aujourd'hui. Seulement, avant, on se posait moins de questions. Ben oui, le père de famille décidait pour tout le monde : sa femme et ses enfants, personne n'avait son mot à dire.
Et dans beaucoup de sociétés aujourd'hui encore, c'est le cas : beaucoup de jeunes filles et de femmes doivent encore se plier au bon vouloir des hommes. Mais ça évolue dans le bon sens !

Dans notre société, beaucoup de filles et de garçons ont connu ces lendemains de soirées où on se réveille à côté de quelqu'un et on se dit "oups, j'aurais peut-être pas dû"... Pour autant, entre regretter et être victime de viol, il y a un fossé, parfois difficile à délimiter. Alors, comment savoir ?

Et puis d'abord, qu'est-ce que c'est un viol ?

Pour la loi française, c'est tout acte de pénétration sexuelle, de quelque nature qu'il soit, commis sur la personne d'autrui par violence, contrainte, menace ou surprise. Donc un viol, c'est pas forcément commis par un homme, et la victime c'est pas forcément une femme. Quant à la pénétration, elle peut avoir lieu dans la bouche ou dans l'anus, pas forcément dans le vagin. Et c'est pas forcément un sexe d'homme qui pénètre, ça peut être un doigt ou un objet...
Maintenant, pour les circonstances :
La violence, on sait ce que c'est : les coups et les cris, c'est ce qu'on voit le plus souvent dans les films.
La contrainte, c'est plus compliqué. C'est pas forcément quelqu'un qui va vous tenir avec ses mains. On peut tenir quelqu'un avec des mots, avec des idées. Si on est trop jeune, par exemple, on va être plus facilement impressionnable.
La menace, on a un peu du mal à la distinguer de la contrainte. Ça peut être un chantage ou une intimidation. Mais ça peut aussi être un cadeau, c'est pas forcément agressif.
Et la surprise, c'est simplement quand on ne s'y attend pas.

La punition pour un viol, elle est très lourde, en France. Ça peut aller jusqu'à 15 ans de prison, et même 20 ans ou 30 dans certains cas. C'est donc pas une mince affaire.

Maintenant, on sait ce que c'est que le viol. Mais on sait toujours pas ce que c'est que le consentement. D'ailleurs, le terme consentement n'apparait pas dans la loi quand on parle de sexualité.

Quand est-ce qu'on est d'accord ? À quoi est-ce qu'on est d'accord ?

D'abord, il faut être assez grand pour pouvoir consentir, on a une vidéo là-dessus, que je vous invite à regarder après. Et il faut aussi être capable de consentir. Si je suis complètement bourré, je vais pas être capable de discernement, c'est-à-dire que je vais pas pouvoir clairement être d'accord. Si je dors, je suis pas non plus capable d'être d'accord.

Si dans mon sommeil, quelqu'un vient me tripoter ou si je décide d'aller tripoter quelqu'un qui dort, c'est pas un viol, il y a pas eu consentement, mais c'est quand même interdit. Ça s'appelle une agression sexuelle. Et si je me mets à poil devant quelqu'un qui l'a pas demandé, ça s'appelle aussi une agression sexuelle, et ça aussi c'est illégal.

En gros, pour que ce soit légal, il faut que l'autre soit clairement d'accord. Et ça, c'est pas toujours facile de le savoir...

title: 7 avril 2024جرائم غامضة | قصة مقتل الشابة الباكستانية |شافيليا احمد |جرائم عالمية,قضايا مثيرة
description:
مرحباً بالجميع، اليوم سوف نلقي نظرة على حالة مروعة أخرى معكم، وهذه هي حالة شافيليا أحمد. كانت هذه حالة من عام 2003 لم تهز بريطانيا فحسب، بل باكستان أيضًا. "شفيليا أحمد" ولدت في 14 يوليو 1986، وهي فتاة بريطانية باكستانية. والد شافيليا، افتخار أحمد، ينحدر في الأصل من منطقة غوجارات في باكستان. وفي سن 20 إلى 22 عامًا تقريبًا، انتقلت افتخار إلى بريطانيا للعمل. وأثناء إقامته هناك لفترة وأثناء العمل، يقع افتخار في حب فتاة أجنبية ويتزوجها. وسرعان ما يصبح أبًا، لكن عندما يعود إلى باكستان ويخبر عائلته بزواجه، لا يقبلونه. ثم تمارس عائلة افتخار ضغوطًا شديدة عليه ليتزوج من فتاة باكستانية أخرى. وعلى الرغم من مقاومة افتخار، إلا أنه استسلم في النهاية لإصرار عائلته، وتزوج من فتاة باكستانية تدعى "فرزانا". بعد الزواج يعود افتخار إلى بريطانيا، وبعد كشف الحقيقة لزوجته الأولى يطلقها. ثم، بعد مرور بعض الوقت، يتصل افتخار بزوجته الثانية، فرزانا، من باكستان إلى بريطانيا.

سعيد و شورى الحلقة 45 👈https://youtu.be/3xPjes6Ew28
(Arabic Dubbing)

سعيد هو الابن الأكبر لعائلة تركية من شبه جزيرة القرم. سعيد الذي أعجب بوالده منذ طفولته، أصبح أحد أفضل ضباط القيصر مثله تماماً و عندما يحين الوقت سيتزوج مع فتاة تركية. شورى هي الابنة الصغرى لعائلة روسية نبيلة، غير سعيدة لأن والدها يعاني من مرض قاتل. تذهب شورى و أختها الكبرى فالنتينا والدهما إلى بتروغراد (سانت بطرسبرغ) للعلاج. عندما يصلون، ينزلون في منزل صديق سعيد السابق بترو وعائلته. بترو الذي ترك مهنته بسبب خطأ ارتكبه في الحرب، يساعد سعيد و شورى على اللقاء ببعضهما. لكن كان بترو يكره سعيد سراً. عند حضور دعوة، يرى سعيد و شورى بعضهما البعض لأول مرة و يقعان في حب بعضهما البعض من النظرة الأولى. بعد هذا الحدث، تنتظرهما مغامرة عظيمة.

title: 3 Major Developments in Execution-Style Murder of Pregnant Teen Hours From Delivery
description:
Savanah Soto was hours away from being induced to give birth to her first child when she and her boyfriend, Matthew Guerra, were shot to death last December. Christopher Preciado, 19, is charged with their murders and his parents are charged with helping move the bodies of Soto and Guerra. This week, Preciado's parents asked that their bail be reduced. Law&Crime's Angenette Levy talks with former prosecutor Josh Ritter about three developments in the case in this episode of Crime Fix — a daily show that delves into the biggest stories in crime.

title: Cold Case Cast Then And Now 2021
description:
Cold Case is an American police procedural crime drama television series which ran on CBS from September 28, 2003 to May 2, 2010. The series revolved around a fictionalized Philadelphia Police Department division that specializes in investigating cold cases.The show is set in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and follows Detective Lilly Rush (Kathryn Morris), a homicide detective with the Philadelphia Police Department, who specializes in "cold cases", or investigations which are no longer being actively pursued by the department. Rush was initially partnered with Detective Chris Lassing (Justin Chambers) in the first five episodes and then with Detective Scotty Valens (Danny Pino) for the remainder of the series. They work under Lieutenant John Stillman (John Finn) and are assisted by other detectives from their squad—Nick Vera (Jeremy Ratchford), Will Jeffries (Thom Barry), and beginning in season three, Kat Miller (Tracie Thoms).
Usually, each episode would focus on a single investigation. All cases involved murders committed in Philadelphia, although investigations occasionally required travel outside the city. Cases were also spread out over much of the previous century, with some as recent as a year or two old and others dating back to the 1910s. Generally, an investigation would begin when the police received a new lead, or "new direction", on a case.

title: Crime Patrol - क्राइम पेट्रोल सतर्क - Ep 779 - Case 19/2017(Part 1)  - 18th Mar, 2017
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SET Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c
In today's episode of Crime Patrol, watch the investigation of a murder case from Mumbai. The police find a dead body of a woman in a housing society. Within a week, the police find another dead body in different location. While investigating, the police find out that the bodies belong to Payal and Swati. The police learn that Payal used to work in a massage centre. Will the police be able to find the murderer? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: جرائم الأتراك مآسي الشعوب
description:
جرائم الأتراك مآسي الشعوب  
لم نعد نذكر تركيا هذه الأيام إلا ومعها مجازر انتهاكات مرتزقة داعش قمع ابتزاز علاقات متوترة مع أوروبا توغل في العراق مرتزقة في ليبيا احتلال في سوريا أحلام أردوغان التوسعية  باتت كوابيس عربية وجرائمه طالت الشعوب العربية لكن هذا ليس بجديد فقبل أن تنتهي خلافتهم المزعومة قتلوا أكثر من مليون أرمني في إبادة هي الأفظع في التاريخ الحديث ونهبوا الدول العربية وقتلوا أهلها وفي العصر الحديث  بقيادة "العثمانيبن الجدد" ترتكب تركيا نفس الجرائم بحق شعوب المنطقة ففي سوريا تدخلوا ليسيطروا على شمالها فسمحوا بتمدد تنظيم داعش ونفذوا عمليات تهجير وتطهير عرقي ضد الأكراد بعد توغلهم بعمليات عسكرية ودعمهم للمرتزقة والارهابيين وتدريبهم تحت إشراف تركي ليستولوا على الشمال بعد تهجير قسري لنحو 200 ألف كردي وفي ليبيا قام أردوغان بالتدخل عبر العميل السراج وحكومة الوفاق غير الشرعية وأرسل مرتزقة وإرهابيين من سوريا ليجد لنفسه موضع قدم في ثروات المتوسط من الغاز والنفط بالإضافة لابتلاع ليبيا وبات يعرف أردوغان بقرصان المتوسط يريد نهب مليارات الدولارات تحت دعوى "إعادة الإعمار" استعمار واحتلال وغزو وإقامة قواعد دائمة عسكرية لتلبية أوهام أردوغان وفي العراق لم يسلم أهل العراق من إجرام الأتراك الذي استخدموا ورقة محاربة "حزب العمال الكردستاني" ليشنوا عملياتهم ضد العراقيين ويتوغلوا في الأراضي العراقية ويؤسسوا قواعد عسكرية لهم وقائع تاريخية وشواهد جارية تبين أن تركيا أردوغان الحالية لا تقل في الإجرام عن أسلافها العثمانيين الذين قتلوا وشردوا الملايين بدعوى "خلافة" مزعومة فلم يسلم العرب من إجرامهم قديما وحديثا

title: Vous allez être choqués…                    #histoirevrai #histoirefolle #horreur #agression
Crimewatch UK - 1990 Rape Cold Case Finally Solved in 2022!
description:
Paul Shakespeare was finally caught for the rape of an 18 year old in bushes along a public footpath in Cheltenham on April 29th 1990. This crimewatch episode aired in January 2008, but despite many leads and DNA taken from the scene, the rapist evaded capture for a further 13 years. 

It wasn't until 2021 that they finally caught their man due to a completely unrelated crime, the possession of an "offensive weapon". Were it not for this crime, the perpetrator would likely never have been caught. 

The victim, now 50, is still suffered psychologically from the event. The rape obviously petrified her at the time, with the mental horror causing her to nearly commit suicide. She still has not told her family due to the sheer violation and embarassment she feels from the rape.

Gary Shakespeare was finally sentenced in January 2022 to 9 years in prison, to the relief of the victim. Let me know what you think in the comments!

The news article can be found here: https://news.sky.com/story/paul-shakespeare-man-jailed-for-1990-rape-of-teenager-who-was-walking-her-dog-12518586

description:
Tejashwi Yadav makes huge remark on Patna LLB Student Murder Case 

पटना में हुई छात्र की हत्या पर बिहार के पूर्व डिप्टी सीएम तेजस्वी यादव ने कहा कि पटना की शहर में लगातार हत्याएं हो रही हैं. पटना और बिहार में जंगल राज आ चुका है. सरकार के लोगों को इसकी गंभीरता जांच करनी चाहिए. दोषी को तुरंत अरेस्ट करके कार्रवाई करनी चाहिए.

On the murder of a student in Patna, former Deputy CM of Bihar Tejashwi Yadav said that murders are happening continuously in the city of Patna. Jungle Raj has arrived in Patna and Bihar. The people of the government should seriously investigate this. The culprit should be arrested immediately and action should be taken.

 #tejashwiyadav #patnallbmurdercase #llbstudentmurderinpatna

title: Chocolate के जरिये कौन कर रहा है अपराध? | CID | TV Serial Latest Episode
description:
Watch the Latest Episode of CID a Hindi TV Serial and one of the most popular tv shows 

Join ACP Pradyuman and his team as they race against time to solve this mysterious case and bring the criminal to justice. Will they be able to crack the case before it's too late? Tune in to find out in this gripping episode of CID.

#cid #cidlatestepisode#cidnewepisode #hinditvserial  #latestepisode #newepisode 
#tvserial #hindiserial #hindishow #tvshow #desicrime

Welcome to the YouTube channel of CID. Get ready for a rollercoaster ride of emotions, and thrilling crime investigations. We bring you short and engaging videos of the most interesting, wanted, and mysterious episodes of CID, both old and new. From horror stories to heart-wrenching emotional episodes, we have it all!

Join us as we take you through the best crime episodes, horror episodes, and the top 10 episodes of CID. Relive the nostalgia with the Purana CID and dive into the latest CID adventures. We are your one-stop destination for all things CID!

But that's not all! We also bring you the best of crime thrillers, crime stories, and crime alerts. Stay updated with the latest episodes of your favorite Hindi TV serials from crime investigations to gripping suspense, our shows will keep you hooked.

So, if you're a fan of Hindi TV serials, crime shows, and thrilling mysteries, this is the channel for you. Don't miss out on the excitement - hit that subscribe button and join us on this thrilling journey. Get ready to immerse yourself in the world of CID and unravel the secrets of Crime Ki Kahani!

About The CID :
The first thrilling investigative series on Indian Television is today one of the most popular shows.  Dramatic and absolutely unpredictable, C.I.D. has captivated viewers over the last eleven years and continues to keep audiences glued to their television sets with its thrilling plots and excitement. Also interwoven in its fast-paced plots are the personal challenges that the C.I.D. team faces with non-stop adventure, tremendous pressure, and risk, all in the name of duty. The series consists of hard-core police procedural stories dealing with investigation, detection, and suspense. The protagonists of the serial are an elite group of police officers belonging to the Crime Investigation Department of the police force, led by ACP Pradyuman, played by the dynamic Shivaji Satam along with Daya and Abhijit. While the stories are plausible, there is an emphasis on dramatic plotting and technical complexities faced by the police. At every stage, the plot throws up intriguing twists and turns to keep the officers on the move as they track criminals, led by the smallest of clues.

भारतीय टेलीविजन पर पहली रोमांचक खोजी श्रृंखला आज सबसे लोकप्रिय शो में से एक है। नाटकीय और बिल्कुल अप्रत्याशित, सी.आई.डी. पिछले ग्यारह वर्षों में दर्शकों को मंत्रमुग्ध कर दिया है और अपने रोमांचक कथानक और उत्साह से दर्शकों को उनके टेलीविजन सेटों से बांधे रखा है। इसके तेज़-तर्रार कथानकों में सी.आई.डी. की व्यक्तिगत चुनौतियाँ भी गुंथी हुई हैं। टीम को ड्यूटी के नाम पर बिना रुके साहसिक कार्य, जबरदस्त दबाव और जोखिम का सामना करना पड़ता है। श्रृंखला में जांच, पता लगाने और रहस्य से संबंधित कठोर पुलिस प्रक्रियात्मक कहानियां शामिल हैं। धारावाहिक के नायक पुलिस बल के अपराध जांच विभाग से संबंधित पुलिस अधिकारियों का एक विशिष्ट समूह हैं, जिसका नेतृत्व एसीपी प्रद्युम्न कर रहे हैं, जिनकी भूमिका दया और अभिजीत के साथ गतिशील शिवाजी सातम ने निभाई है। हालाँकि कहानियाँ विश्वसनीय हैं, लेकिन इसमें नाटकीय कथानक और पुलिस द्वारा सामना की जाने वाली तकनीकी जटिलताओं पर भी जोर दिया गया है। हर चरण में, कथानक में दिलचस्प मोड़ आते हैं और अधिकारी छोटे-छोटे सुरागों के आधार पर अपराधियों का पता लगाने में सक्रिय रहते हैं।

Cast:
Shivaji Satam as ACP Pradyuman
Dinesh Phadnis as Inspector Fredricks aka Freddy
Ashutosh Gowariker as Sr. Inspector Virendra
Dayanand Shetty as Sr. Inspector Daya

title: 11 अपराध नियन्त्रण
ME VICIOU E ME MAT0U? CASO LORENZA PINHO - INVESTIGAÇÃO CRIMINAL
description:
Lorenza de Pinho era casada com o promotor mineiro André Luiz Garcia de Pinho há mais de dez anos. #Mãe de cinco filhos, morando em Belo Horizonte, em Minas Gerais, Lorenza passava por um período de depressão, especialmente depois que o padrão de vida de sua família caiu e todos tiveram que mudar de um amplo apartamento para um bem menor. Afastada pelo marido de sua irmã gêmea e de seus pais, Lorenza vivia uma vida escondida. No seu novo endereço, nenhum vizinho a conhecia, nem nunca tinha a visto pelo prédio. Muitos moradores sequer sabiam que ali vivia uma mulher que seria, em breve, assassinada possivelmente pelo #marido. André é acusado de #matar Lorenza simulando uma autointoxicação por remédios e álcool. A verdade só seria descoberta graças ao pai de Lorenza que não acreditava na morte natural de sua filha e conseguiu acionar a polícia antes que Lorenza fosse cremada. 

No IML, descobriu-se a verdade: Lorenza havia sido #asfixiada, vítima de #feminicidio. 

A história vai tomando contornos ainda mais macabros, sem qualquer explicação, teria o promotor Andre, o marido, tirado todo o sangue da esposa?
No corpo humano existem 5 litros de sangue, no de Lorenza foram constatados apenas 25 ml. O plano de André não foi tão perfeito assim.

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Part 246! #trial #truecrime #court #live #murdernews #shorts #fyp #murdermystery #crime #crimestory
description:
Shanda Vanderark questioned by her attorney on the witness stand. See parts before this and the parts I'll post after this for more context, they are posted in chronological order. I'll post the remaining parts of her full testimony in the next days. I'll also post the complete testimony of her son Paul Ferguson on the witness stand after that. He was found guilty as well.

If you liked this video, please leave a like, subscribe, comment, share & set the notification bell to ALL so you won't miss any new videos & premieres! You can now become a member of the channel too and give Super Thanks if you liked a video! This wil help me to continue making videos.

Please let me know what you think about her testimony in the comments below.

Heartbreaking.. Michigan woman Shanda Vander Ark was found guilty of murder and child abuse in the starvation death of her disabled 15-year-old son who weighed just 69 pounds. 

The Muskegon County Circuit Court jury deliberated just over an hour before convicting Shanda Vander Ark, 44, of Norton Shores in the July 6, 2022, death of Timothy Ferguson. 

An autopsy determined the teenager died from malnourishment and hypothermia. The medical examiner ruled his death a homicide. 

Shanda's son Paul Ferguson was also convicted and has been sentenced to 30-100 years in prison. Paul Ferguson received the sentence after pleading guilty in December to one count of first-degree child abuse in the death of his 15-year-old brother Timothy Ferguson. Paul faced a potential sentence of up to life in prison, but the sentencing guidelines call for a term of 9-15 years. However, the judge's discretion was that this case was so serious that it called for him to be sentenced to 30-100 years. 

As part of a plea deal with the Muskegon County Prosecutor's Office, Paul testified against his mother, Shanda Vander Ark, at her trial in December. 

Vander Ark was convicted of neglecting Timothy so severely that he died in the basement of their home. Timothy was described by his mother as having high-functioning autism, ADHD, bipolar disorder, and several other mental ailments. 

According to Chief Trial Attorney for Muskegon County Matt Roberts, their office also agreed not to bring further charges against Paul, such as murder, in exchange for his guilty plea. 

#justice #livestream #asmr #sentences #sentimental #testimony #testify #witness

It's the city of the iconic Golden Gate, with its steep, winding streets and is, for many, the gay mecca. San Francisco has always been considered one of the most beautiful and diverse cities in the world, with enormous potential for growth and entertainment, but things may be changing. Lack of security, drugs and homelessness are plaguing the city so beloved by such greats as Rudyard Kipling, Frank Lloyd Wright and Tony Bennet. Many believe it is descending into the abyss already familiar to Detroit. Yet San Francisco shows no signs of surrender. What are the problems afflicting San Francisco today? Why does it seem to be following the same path as Detroit? How can the city government stop this drift? Today we tell you.

बाल विवाह अपराध है या नहीं?

बाल विवाह कठोर कारावास के साथ दंडनीय अपराध है , जो 2 वर्ष तक का हो सकता है , या 1 लाख रुपये तक जुर्माना या दोनों हो सकता है । हालाँकि , एक महिला को इस अधिनियम के तहत कैद नहीं किया जा सकता है तथापि , जुर्माने के माध्यम से महिला को दंडित किया जा सकता है । अधिनियम के तहत अपराध संज्ञेय और गैर - जमानती हैं । संज्ञेय अपराध का अर्थ- संज्ञेय अपराध एक आपराधिक अपराध है जिसमें पुलिस को एफआईआर दर्ज करने और अदालत द्वारा वारंट जारी किए बिना एक आरोपी को गिरफ्तार करने का अधिकार है । गैर - जमानती अपराध यदि किसी व्यक्ति को ऐसे अपराध के लिए गिरफ्तार किया जाता है जो गैर - जमानती है , तो उस मामले में अदालत अपने विवेक पर जमानत दे सकती है ।

title: Doctor Accused of Poisoning Wife Identified as 'Widower' Before Murder: Police
description:
Former Mayo Clinic pharmacist Dr. Connor Bowman is charged with murdering his wife, Betty Bowman, last August. Police say Bowman poisoned Betty with medicine he ordered online and then tried to cover his tracks. Detectives now say Bowman was calling himself a widower before Betty died. title: وثائقي تحقيقات جرائم القتل.. قتلة! متسلسلون يثيران الذعر في كاليفورنيا والسلطات تواجه تحدياً صعباً !
description:
مرحبًا بكم في وثائقي مثير وملحمي يلقي الضوء على جرائم القتل والتحقيقات الشاقة في ولاية كاليفورنيا. في هذا الوثائقي، سنتعمق في قصة مخيفة تحكي عن قتلة متسلسلين يثيران الذعر والهلع في كاليفورنيا.
بينما تواجه السلطات تحديًا صعبًا في مطاردة هؤلاء الجناة المروعين، سنستكشف خلف الكواليس للتحقيقات والتكتيكات التي تستخدمها الشرطة للقبض على هؤلاء المجرمين ووضع حد لجرائمهم الشنيعة.


هذا الوثائقي سيأخذك في رحلة مثيرة وملحمية، مليئة بالتوتر والتشويق، حيث ستتابع معنا التطورات الأخيرة في هذه القضية المثيرة. لا تفوت الفرصة للانغماس في عالم الجريمة والتحقيق، واكتشاف ما وراء الأسرار والألغاز التي تحيط بجرائم القتل في كاليفورنيا.
انضم إلينا الآن وكن جزءًا من هذه الرحلة الغامضة والمثيرة، حيث سنسعى جاهدين لكشف الحقيقة وتحقيق العدالة.

Read is accused of murdering her boyfriend, Boston Police Officer John O’Keefe, whose body was found in the snow outside of another Boston officer’s home in Canton, Massachusetts.

title: Cold Case: Der Göhrde-Mörder Kurt-Werner Wichmann | Achtung Fahndung
description:
📺 „Achtung Fahndung“ – jeden Dienstag, 22.00 Uhr bei BILD im TV und auf bild.tv.


Sie nannten ihn „Göhrde-Mörder“ oder auch „blonde Bestie“: Friedhofsgärtner Kurt-Werner Wichmann († 43) tötete 1989 fünf Menschen – mindestens, denn es könnte noch Dutzende mehr Opfer geben.

Private Ermittler und die Polizei Lüneburg sind sich zudem noch immer sicher: Wichmann hatte einen bis heute unbekannten Komplizen. Bis heute sucht die Polizei Lüneburg im Ermittlungskomplex-Göhrde nach Wichmanns mutmaßlichem Mittäter.

Die Wahrheit nahm Wichmann mit ins Grab: 1993 nahm er sich in der U-Haft das Leben.


Die unheimlichen Morde im Göhrde-Forst
▶︎Am 21. Mai 1989 verschwindet das Ehepaar Ursula und Peter Reinold bei einem Ausflug in den Lüneburger Staatsforst. Erst drei Wochen später, am 12. Juni, finden Blaubeersammler ihre stark verwesten Leichen. Sie eilen zum nahe gelegenen Forsthaus Röthen – und alarmieren die Polizei. Auf dem Weg aus dem Staatsforst begegnen sie einen verdächtigen Mann. Ist es der Göhrde-Mörder?

▶︎ Während die Polizei die leblosen Körper birgt und die Spuren sichert, schlägt Wichman nur 756 Meter entfernt wieder zu und tötet Ingrid Warmbier und ihren Liebhaber Bernd-Michael Köpping.

description:

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupzmzTUmYFZJe4UhLkm23APh

Relive the best episodes of your favorite crime-thriller show, Crime Patrol.  

About the show:
--------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Crime Patrol - क्राइम पेट्रोल सतर्क - Ep 786 - Case 23 / 2017 (Part 2) -2nd Apr, 2017
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SET Channel : https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1
Click to watch all the episodes of Crime Patrol Satark - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupza0aEZ_FKj0mBguCdtwU_c
Today's episode continues with the search of Shikha’s murderer. While investigating the case, the police find out that Shikha’s family had prohibited her from going to her college in the past. Sumit clears it to the police that he has not killed Shikha. Will the police be able to find the murderer? Stay tuned in to find the answer.
Crime Patrol coming back in its 4th season attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved.Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?'I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there.In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. Husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there.Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy.Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. May be, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

CID is an Indian detective television anthology series about India's Crime Investigation Department, created by B. P. title: Seine-Saint-Denis : l'agression de deux policiers après un contrôle routier
description:
Deux policiers ont été agressés par une quinzaine de personnes après un contrôle routier dimanche à Aulnay-sous-Bois (Seine-Saint-Denis). 
Une enquête pour violences sur personnes dépositaires de l'ordre public a été confiée au commissariat local, et une personne a été interpellée.

Des images de vidéo amateur, diffusées sur les réseaux sociaux, montrent les deux motards, dont l'un est à terre, aux prises avec un individu pendant que deux autres hommes leur assènent des coups de pied.

title: Fourteen Trump Officials Are Currently Accused Of Criminal Conduct
description:
According to the latest count, fourteen different Trump cabinet members and White House officials are either under investigation for violations of federal law, or they have been accused of breaking federal laws. The laws that these officials broke are all the same: The Hatch Act. And while it may seem small, it just goes to show that this administration has no regard for the rule of law. Ring of Fire's Farron Cousins discusses this.

Link - https://www.alternet.org/2020/10/pompeo-under-investigation/?fbclid=IwAR2X6FGqoUuEIdsjKJYpZ3tqnvzyScuNrTg7srWLf-2rZ_8piYxG5r6yzls

According to an analysis. There were at least 14 different members of the Trump administration who are either currently under criminal investigation or who have been accused of criminal conduct. And each  one of these 14 people, six of them are cabinet officials. The other eight are just regular administration officials. Uh, the law that all of these people have been accused of breaking is the hatch act, which is a federal law. So a violation of the hatch act is a violation of federal law. Here are just a few of the people named, uh, that have been accused of this, uh, the cabinet secretaries. These would be secretary of state, Mike Pompeo, attorney general, bill BARR, education, secretary Betsy Devoss, interior, secretary David Bernhardt, agriculture, secretary, Sonny Perdue, and acting Homeland security. Secretary Chad Wolf. You also of course have other administration officials, including, but not limited to white house, press secretary Kaley McInerney, and nobody knows why the hell she's there. 

Ivanka Trump with a staggering 48 Ivanka Trump has 48 different noted violations of the hatch act. So for anybody not familiar with this, the hatch act is the federal law that says a government official can not advocate for or against any political party or candidate or issue from their official capacity. Working for the federal government. The exceptions include obviously the vice president and the president of the United States. Anybody else you can't use your official position to go out there and say, vote for Trump or don't vote for Biden. These people have done that. And many, many more things over the last few months alone. Now here's the thing. You may think that violating the hatch act like, okay, they're not supposed to go out there and say, Hey, vote for this person or don't vote for that person. It does seem kind of silly, right? 

I mean, is this going to be a felony, you know, reacts, you're going to lock anybody up over this. We're already over incarcerated as a nation, as it is. You know, let's, let's not, you know, kind of nitpick some of this stuff here. Well, here's the thing nobody's going to  jail for these hatch act violations. The office of special counsel was only able to essentially recommend disciplinary action to the president, much like they did with, uh, Kellyanne Conway. When they said, Hey, she keeps breaking the law. You need to fire her. And Trump said, okay, I'm not going to do anything. Thanks for your report. And that was the end of it. So that's essentially what would happen. But folks, the point is all of these individuals know what they're doing. They know that this is the law and it doesn't matter if it's a minor law, doesn't matter if it's serious. All they know it and they're making the conscious choice to break it. 

And the reason I like to bring that up is because you think about any video, you've seen any video where you have an unarmed black person or maybe a mildly armed black person. You know, they got a pocket knife and a bunch of cops with guns pointed at them. And the cop says, you know, Oh, stop walking forward. And they just keep slowly walking forward and they get shot a hundred times. And her laying there dead on the pavement, the Republican response is who he should have just obeyed the law.

title: Trump attorneys descend into disaster at criminal trial
description:
Former President Donald Trump’s lawyer may be losing what many attorneys would consider one of the most important things to have: credibility. It’s no secret that the former president might not be the easiest client to represent but Trump’s attorney, Todd Blanche, might be risking his reputation to do so. Judge Juan Merchan seemed frustrated with Blanche during a hearing this week to determine whether or not Trump violated a gag order in his first criminal trial. In response to Blanche’s claim that Trump was attempting to comply with the judge’s orders, Judge Merchan told the attorney that he’s losing credibility with the court. MSNBC's Brian Tyler Cohen takes a closer look at what went down and what this could mean for Trump’s lawyers and their reputations. title: Criminals Who Are STILL On the Run in 2024...
description:
On February 21st, Australian police finally caught the convicted murderer, Graham Potter, who had been on the run for 12 years. A convicted killer, he had been evading conspiracy to murder charges since 2010. Investigators later found that he had attempted to change his appearance and demeanour to avoid detection - but was eventually found in a dilapidated house in Ravenshoe, in the far north of Queensland. Potter, however, is one of many criminals who go on the run and manage to avoid capture for years, and sometimes even decades. In today’s video, we’ll be exploring two terrifying cases of criminals still on the run.

title: A Killer From A Cold Case Uncovered By A Psychic? | Psychic Investigators | Full Episode
description:
A detective asks a psychic to help him with a case that he has been unable to solve. The psychic offers her help with an older case of his instead, provides some new details, and possibly uncovers the murderer.

Do you believe in psychics and their contribution to the investigation?

Psychic Investigators - From Season 1 Episode 3 "Margie Calciano": Detective Robert Wanner consults psychic Lauren Thibodeau to help with a case that has left him stumped.  Surprisingly she instead offers clues on a cold case that’s been worrying Wanner for years.  Thibodeau’s visions offer obscure clues: she sees a map with a bead of light traveling along a highway from New York to Chicago, a truck driver and the Brooklyn bridge.  Using old-fashioned police work, Wanner deciphers the clues one by one which lead him to a killer several states away.

Real-life detective thrillers take on a supernatural turn in Psychic Investigators, a documentary series about actual dramatic crimes that are solved through the unlikely combination of hi-tech detective work and the paranormal powers of a psychic.

In each episode, one amazing story is told from two very different points of view – the detective and the psychic. Featuring crimes committed in the USA and the United Kingdom, Psychic Investigators juxtaposes the psychic’s story - coloured with emotion, empathy and mystery, with the cop’s tale – dominated by logic, evidence and reason. 

These spellbinding stories, interwoven with suspense, intrigue, and twists and turns, feature stylized dramatic reconstructions, unique archive and compelling interviews with key characters. Playing like supernatural thrillers, these shows make the hairs on the back of your neck stand on end.

title: Ventura PD solves 33-year-old cold case homicide
description:
After over three decades, the Ventura Police Department (VPD) has made a significant breakthrough in the 1991 murder case of Danielle Clause. Using advanced forensic genetic genealogy techniques, law enforcement has identified Larry Devon Welch as the perpetrator, which is a pivotal moment in resolving this long-standing mystery.

“Through extensive collaboration with local and national law enforcement agencies and nonprofits, it’s with great pride that I share this success story,” said Ventura Police Chief Darin Schindler. “From the initial investigation in 1991 to recent advancements in forensic techniques, I’m honored to highlight the perseverance of detectives as they continued to seek justice for the victim and her family.”

On July 16, 1991, the body of 42-year-old Clause was found on the hillside located at the top of Tioga Drive near downtown Ventura. The autopsy showed that she had been sexually assaulted and had died due to multiple blunt-force injuries to her head. Once investigators at the time explored every avenue, the case was suspended and considered cold.

In 2021, Ventura Police detectives and forensic specialists retested crime scene evidence for DNA. Forensic genetic genealogy was pursued, and a family tree was developed. Phenotyping was used to verify distinct characteristics of the suspect, and after collecting family DNA samples, Larry Welch was positively identified. 

Welch passed away in 1999. There was no known connection between Welch and Clause at the time of her murder.

“My sister was so much more than a victim of a brutal murder. She was artist, a daughter, a sister, a mother, and a wife. She was a good person with a mighty soul, and she was taken way too young,” shared Marcie Forte, Danielle’s sister. “I didn’t really believe that the police were going to solve this, because there are other crimes being committed all the time. I was proven wrong because the Ventura Police and everyone associated with this cold case did a phenomenal job and I am so grateful. I’m so grateful that I lived to see at least a meter of justice and that they found out who did this.”

The Ventura Police Department’s unwavering commitment to securing justice for victims and their families endures, regardless of the elapsed time. Presently, VPD has over 25 cold cases, spanning homicides, missing persons, and unidentified deceased individuals.

For more information about each case, visit CityofVentura.ca.gov/ColdCases. If you have any new information, please email coldcase@venturapd.org.

title: Agression du 22 novembre 1970 : « elle a eu lieu avec l’aval de Sékou Touré », dit Aliou Barry
description:
La Guinée commémore ce lundi, 22 novembre 2021, le 51ème anniversaire de l’agression portugaise du 22 novembre 1970 sur son territoire. A cette journée de souvenirs douloureux et d’émotion qui font remonter les tristes souvenirs de cette tentative de déstabilisation du régime Sékou Touré ourdi par une puissance colonel (le Portugal), mais aussi la vague de répressions orchestrée en Guinée par le régime en place contre « les complices » de cette agression, Guineematin.com est à la rencontre de Aliou Barry, chercheur et directeur du CAES (centre d’appui et d’études stratégiques). Notre interlocuteur assure que l’attaque portugaise contre la Guinée a bel et bien eu lieu. Mais, il est aussi formel sur le fait que le chef de l’Etat guinéen de l’époque, Sékou Touré, était informé de ladite attaque. Et, il a voulu faire de cette agression un atout pour éliminer des adversaires politiques.

« Le 22 novembre est une date qui a permis à Sékou Touré d’opérer une large purge au sein de l’élite guinéenne, qu’elle soit à la fois militaire ou politique. Aujourd’hui, toute la documentation existe pour dire que la nuit du dimanche 21 au 22 novembre, il y a 6 navires portugais qui ont accosté aux larges de Conakry. Mais, avant l’agression du 22 novembre, les Guinéens de l’extérieur s'étaient regroupés au sein du Front de libération nationale de la Guinée qui était basé à Dakar et qui était dirigé par monsieur David Soumah. C’est lui et d’autres Guinéens qui étaient contre le régime en place qui ont cherché à renverser Sékou Touré. Il s’avère qu’à l’époque, en Guinée, le PAIGC (Parti Africain de l’Indépendance de la Guinée et du Cap-Vert) avait une base arrière en Guinée et était soutenu par Sékou Touré dans la perspective de la libération de la Guinée Bissau et des Îles du Cap-Vert. Et c’est Amical Cabral qui dirigeait ce mouvement basé à Conakry. Il se trouvait aussi que pendant ces actions de libération, le PAIGC a fait prisonnier quelques portugais notamment le maire de Lisbonne. Donc, le gouvernement portugais de l’époque s’est rapproché de l’opposition guinéenne (le Front de libération de la Guinée) et ils ont envisagé une action à la fois de libération de leurs détenus et aider la diaspora guinéenne à renverser Sékou Touré. C’est ainsi que pendant des mois, il y a eu des réunions à Lisbonne, à Dakar et à Abidjan et près de 250 Guinéens ont été mobilisés. On les a envoyés aux îles Soga au Cap-Vert où avec l’aide du gouvernement portugais, il y a eu 6 navires qui ont accosté à Conakry à 2 heures du matin, la nuit du 22 novembre », explique Aliou Barry.

« Selon la documentation qu’on a trouvé, il y a eu mésentente. Le Portugal tenait à libérer ses détenus politiques et les Guinéens voulaient profiter pour renverser Sékou Touré. Mais, toute la documentation en notre possession prouve que Sékou Touré a été prévenu par la CIA qu’il y aura une agression en Guinée. D’ailleurs, à 2 heures du matin, quand les gens ont débarqué, curieusement, seule la présidence était éclairée. Le premier groupe qui est venu aux Cases Belle-vue n’a pas trouvé Sékou Touré. Un autre groupe est parti libérer les prisonniers politiques du Camp Boïro, le 3ème groupe est parti au siège du PAIGC où un allemand a été assassiné. Le 4ème est parti à l’aéroport de Conakry sans trouver ni Mig, ni avion. Il a décidé de ne rien faire. Il s’est avéré pendant ce temps que tous les moyens de communication ont une défaillance. Ce qui est aussi curieux, c'est que ceux qui ont débarqué à Conakry n’ont trouvé aucune résistance, parce qu’à l’époque, même à l’interne, le régime de Sékou Touré était décrié. L’opération a foiré et vers 8 heures du matin, les portugais ont décidé de se rembarquer avec les guinéens qui étaient disponibles dont le commandant Diallo Tierno qui dirigeait l’opération et monsieur Siradio Diallo qui était présent. Malheureusement, nombreux sont ceux qui sont restés à terre et ils ont été arrêtés par la milice populaire de Sékou Touré qui en a fait toute une montagne », a indiqué Aliou Barry.

« Sékou Touré s’est servi de cet évènement pour déclarer qu’il y a eu une agression contre la Guinée. C’est vrai que les portugais ont débarqué ; mais, les Guinéens aussi ont profité de l’occasion pour le renverser. Et, à partir de janvier 1971, Sékou Touré a profité pour orchestrer une véritable purge au niveau de la classe politique. Dans toutes les villes de Guinée, il y a eu des pendaisons. A Conakry, au pont 8 novembre, il y a eu 4 hautes personnalités qui ont été pendues. C’est vrai qu'il y a eu une agression ; mais, c’est vrai aussi que Sékou Touré était au courant de ce qui allait arriver. Cependant, il ne savait pas que les Guinéens allaient en profiter pour le renverser. C’est aussi une page de l’histoire guinéenne qui est très sombre. Cela fait partie du devoir de mémoire et je crois que les historiens doivent rouvrir ce dossier en toute objectivité pour que les générations futures sachent ce qui s’est passé le 22 novembre 1970 »

title: Der Fall Iris Hans, Cold Case aus Mayen: Warum musste 14-Jährige sterben?
description:
Cold Cases - Ungelöste Fälle der Polizei Rheinland-Pfalz 
Der Fall Iris Hans 
Am 31. August 1978 wird die 14-jährige Iris Hans mit 26 Stichen ermordet. Bis heute fehlt jede Spur zum Täter. Wir haben mit den Geschwistern des Opfers sowie dem damaligen Ermittler Horst Eckhardt und dem heutigen Ermittler Lothar Schenk über den Fall gesprochen. 
Haben Sie Hinweise zu dem Mord? Kennen Sie Mitwisser, die sich damals nicht mit der Polizei in Verbindung gesetzt haben? Sind Ihnen an Menschen starke Wesensveränderungen aufgefallen? Die etwa mit ihrem sozialen Umfeld gebrochen haben, unerwartet weggezogen sind oder psychisch auffällig waren?

About Crime Patrol : 
-----------------------------------
Crimes tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol - Satark Rahe will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Corté a mi novio por ser un CRIMINAL
description:
Mi novio causó un accidente y fue encarcelado, ¿ustedes lo habrían dejado?
#storytime #historias #abrohilo #criminal 
Inspiración: @diario.personal 


Iba caminando a la fiesta de cumpleaños de  mi amiga Yaqui, cuando

.-¡Ah! 

.-¿Estás bien? 

.-¡Eres un tonto! Arruinaste mi vestido nuevo. Deberías aprender a manejar

.-Y tú, preciosa, deberías fijarte por donde vas. 


Era nueva en el pueblo, y quería causar una buena impresión, pero me veía asquerosa. 


.-Hola Yaqui. ¡Feliz cumpleaños! 

.-¡Dina! ¿Qué te pasó? 

.-Nada, un baboso en moto me asustó de camino acá. 


Decidí disfrutar la fiesta, cuando… 


.-Creo que ya conoces a todos. ¿Recuerdas a Roy? Mi novio. 

.-Y él es Jacobo, mi hermano, pero no creo que quieras conocerlo, es un dolor de cabeza. 

.-¿Es tu hermano? ¡Es el tonto de la moto! 


.-Que tal chicas. 


No pude contener mi coraje al verlo. 


.-¿Cómo es que te dejan manejar una moto? ¡Imprudente! 

.-Olvídalo, no vale la pena. 


.-Pues al menos yo no cruzo la calle sin mirar el semáforo, preciosa.  


Jacobo era el típico chico malo que todos evitaban. 


Solo quería mantenerme alejada de él, 


pero empecé a encontrármelo por todos lados, 


hasta en la sopa, literalmente. 
 




.-¡Hola! ¿Necesitas que te lleve? 



.-No gracias, tonto. 

.-Está bien, tonta. Adiós. 


Pero aceptémoslo, ¿qué chica no siente debilidad por un chico malo? 


.-¿Te gustaría dar una vuelta? 


.-No insistas…

bueno, solo un poquito. 



Luego me dí cuenta que detrás de esa fachada de malote, 

había un chico tierno e inteligente. 


.-Y esa de ahí, es la constelación de qué perro hilo 



Y después de varias citas, Jacobo me preguntó si quería ser su novia, y pues…le dije que sí. 


Me sentía muy feliz con él, pero no todos opinaban igual.



.-Jacobo no te conviene, amiga, te romperá el corazón. Hazme caso. 

.-Te prohíbo salir con ese muchacho ¿entendido? Tiene fama de problemático. 


Ni siquiera sus padres creían en él.  


.-Dina, eres una chica muy linda, seguro encontrarás a alguien mejor para ti

.-¿Qué? 

.-Jacobo es…difícil. 

.-Y no nos gustaría que te metieras en problemas por su culpa. 

No podía creer lo que su propia familia pensaba de él. 
 
Pero luego entendí porque. 


.-Debo irme, hija. Hubo un accidente en el centro.


.-¿Qué pasó? 



Yaquí me habló para decirme que Jacobo había robado el auto de sus padres. 


.-¡Se estrelló con una tienda de los papás de Roy! Ahora sí que está en graves problemas. 

.-¡No! Esto no puede ser cierto. 


Salí corriendo para ver lo que estaba pasando con mis propios ojos. 

.-Jacobo es inocente. Él jamás hubiera hecho algo así. 


.-Hija, lo acaba de confesar todo. 


.-¿Qué? 


No podía creerlo. 

.-¿En verdad lo hiciste? Pensé que ya habías dejado tus jueguitos tontos de chico malo. 

.-Dina, yo-

.-¿Sabes qué? Así déjalo. ¿Cómo pude creer en alguien como tú? Hasta nunca.
Me sentí traicionada, así que no volví a verlo y traté de olvidarme de él. 





.-Lo enviarán a prisión por 2 años.


.-¿En serio? 

.-Y tuvo suerte. Una persona casi pierde la vida. 


Los siguientes meses 

solo me concentré en mis estudios.

Salía con Yaqui y Roy, pero a menudo pensaba en Jacobo, y me preguntaba cómo estaba. 



.-Hasta mañana. 

.-¿Estás hablando con Dina?  


.-¿Qué fue eso? ¿Es Jacobo? 


.-Shhh, hazte para allá. Sí, aquí está. Salió antes. 

.-¡¿Qué?! ¡¿Por qué no me dijiste?! 


Pero ahora ya no sabía si quería volver a verlo. Me preguntaba si en verdad lo conocía. 



.-Hola. ¿Me extrañaste? 

.-Osh, Jacobo, ¿qué haces aquí? 

.-Sí, creo. Te ves…diferente.


Estaba muy confundida. 

.-Lo que necesitas es ocupar tu mente en otras cosas. 

.-¿Tú crees? 



.-Tu y yo nos prepararemos para irnos juntas a la universidad. Me urge irme de este pueblo. 

.-¡Siii, qué gran idea! 


Estudiaba día y noche con Yaqui, 


así que casi no nos quedaba tiempo libre. 


.-¿Y qué hay de mi, Jaqui? ¡Soy tu novio!



.-Lo sé, Roy, pero es una gran oportunidad para superarnos ¿no crees? 


.-¿Y qué pasará con nosotros? Yo tengo que quedarme aquí a trabajar con mis padres.  
 


.-¿Y a este intenso qué le pasa? 

.-...creo que no durmió bien…jeje. 


Yo seguía pensando en Jacobo. No podía evitarlo, 


pero él parecía empeñarse en buscar problemas. 


.-¿Qué pasó aquí? 


.-¡Alguien arruinó los documentos para nuestra beca universitaria!

.-¡No puede ser! Seguro Jacobo quiere vengarse de mí por terminar nuestra relación. 

.-Si, eso debe ser.



Y ahí no paró el asunto. 

.-¡Ayuda!


.-¿Qué estás haciendo? 

.-Espera, Dina, no entiendes- 

.-Entiendo que todo era mejor cuando estabas lejos. ¡Ahora vete! 


Jacobo desapareció después de lo que le dije. Quizás había sido muy dura.  


.-¿Sabes dónde podría estar? 

.-No lo sé, no ha venido a casa en días, pero no es la primera vez que lo hace. Ya estamos acostumbrados. 


Me sentía responsable por lo que Jacobo pudiera hacer. 


Después de todo, yo había sido la última en tratarlo mal.

.-¿Jacobo?

.-¡La moto de Jacobo!

About Crime Patrol:
Crime Patrol attempts to bring stories of crime happening all around the country. The episodes showcase a fictional representation of real-life crime cases in India. Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. The series opens its viewers’ minds to these cases by making them aware of the crime around them. Crime Patrol has not only focused on creating awareness about crimes but has also aimed to help the victims depicted in the episodes.

क्राइम पेट्रोल देश भर में हो रहे अपराध की कहानियाँ सामने लाने का प्रयास करता है। ये एपिसोड भारत में वास्तविक जीवन के अपराध के मामलों का काल्पनिक प्रतिनिधित्व दिखाते हैं। अपराध जो हमें बताते हैं, हमें सावधान रहने की जरूरत है, हमें सतर्क रहने की जरूरत है। अपराध जो हमें बताते हैं कि जिंदगियां बचाई जा सकती थीं। यह श्रृंखला अपने दर्शकों को उनके आसपास होने वाले अपराध के बारे में जागरूक करके इन मामलों के बारे में उनके दिमाग को खोलती है। क्राइम पेट्रोल ने न केवल अपराधों के बारे में जागरूकता पैदा करने पर ध्यान केंद्रित किया है, बल्कि एपिसोड में दर्शाए गए पीड़ितों की मदद करने का भी लक्ष्य रखा है।

title: Affaire Bary: L'Heure du Crime
description:
26 mars 2004 il est 11h35, Laurent Bary, 35 ans, éleveur de poulets rentre chez lui à Lanneau près de Dijon. Alors qu´il pénètre dans le salon il découvre une scène d´horreur, sa femme Valérie, 38ans, gît au sol, elle a le crâne fracassé et a été sauvagement poignardée de treize coups de couteau. Immédiatement alertés les gendarmes trouvent près du corps de Valérie, l´arme du crime, un couteau de boucher dont la lame mesure plus de vingt centimètres. Mais aucune empreinte, ni aucun ADN ne sera retrouvé, comme si le meurtrier avait miraculeusement effacé toute trace de son passage. Qui pouvait en vouloir à cette aide-soignante sans histoire ? Interrogé Laurent Bary a un solide alibi, il a passé la matinée à livrer des poulets dans la région et l´autopsie révèle que son épouse a été tuée une heure avant que l´homme ne rentre au domicile conjugal. Très vite l´enquête s´oriente sur l´hypothèse d´un cambriolage qui aurait mal tourné car plusieurs objets personnels de la victime ont disparu. 18 mois s´écoulent, jusqu'à ce que la montre de Valérie Bary soit retrouvée à quelques kilomètres seulement de la scène du crime, au domicile d´un proche du mari !
Réalisateur : Virginie Selvetti

title: Cold case murder of Sydney woman Lynette White | Australian Story
description:
The unsolved 1973 stabbing murder of young Sydney mother Lynette White terrified the community and has baffled police for more than 40 years. 

Lynette’s husband Paul discovered her body when he returned home from work and has lobbied tirelessly in the years since to have the murder re-investigated.

Now police have reopened the case and new leads have emerged. But the question remains: Who killed Lynette White?
