title: Crime Patrol | Motive | Justice For Women | Full Episode
description:
Click here to Subscribe to SetIndia Channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/setindia?sub_confirmation=1

Click to watch all the special episodes of Crime Patrol:
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzufeTFnhupyqFyV-YnilX3Qfa9tSEHad&disable_polymer=true

Watch special episodes of Crime Patrol handpicked from different corners of India.

About the show Crime Patrol:
------------------------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear of, either warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened'.Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like the way he looks at me', 'I don’t like the way he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy'. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare which unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house a husband and wife argue, fight. A vessel comes flying, a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance that keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Babysitter Cold Case Trial: Prosecution Closing Argument
description:
"Now he's saying, 'Back in 1990, I went through this before, and nothing bit me on the ass. So there's a very good chance it won't this time.'"

Prosecutor Stephanie Russell told the jury that the case was simple and that DNA evidence clearly identified Joseph Zieler as the killer.

title: DNA Testing in West Memphis 3 Case #shorts
description:
In this episode of All Things Crime, Jared Bradley and George Jared delve deep into the unsettling case of the West Memphis Three. With meticulous detail, they recount the tragic murders of three young boys while visiting the site where the boys lived and where their bodies were found. They discuss the wrongful imprisonment of three teenagers and the subsequent legal battles that followed. From initial suspicions to recent developments in DNA testing, this discussion sheds light on the complexities and controversies surrounding this notorious case

https://www.m-vac.com/

All Things Crime is a new, comprehensive video series that will explore every aspect of crime and the ensuing investigation, one video interview at a time.  The host, Jared Bradley, is the President of M-Vac Systems, which is a wet-vacuum based forensic DNA collection system, and has experience traveling the world training all levels of law enforcement and crime lab DNA analysts in using the M-Vac to help solve crime.  Along the way he has met people from all walks of life and experience in investigating crimes, so is putting that knowledge to use in another way by sharing it in these videos.

About The CID :
The first thrilling investigative series on Indian Television is today one of the most popular shows.  Dramatic and absolutely unpredictable, C.I.D. has captivated viewers over the last eleven years and continues to keep audiences glued to their television sets with its thrilling plots and excitement. Also interwoven in its fast-paced plots are the personal challenges that the C.I.D. team faces with non-stop adventure, tremendous pressure, and risk, all in the name of duty. The series consists of hard-core police procedural stories dealing with investigation, detection, and suspense. The protagonists of the serial are an elite group of police officers belonging to the Crime Investigation Department of the police force, led by ACP Pradyuman, played by the dynamic Shivaji Satam along with Daya and Abhijit. While the stories are plausible, there is an emphasis on dramatic plotting and technical complexities faced by the police. At every stage, the plot throws up intriguing twists and turns to keep the officers on the move as they track criminals, led by the smallest of clues.

भारतीय टेलीविजन पर पहली रोमांचक खोजी श्रृंखला आज सबसे लोकप्रिय शो में से एक है। नाटकीय और बिल्कुल अप्रत्याशित, सी.आई.डी. पिछले ग्यारह वर्षों में दर्शकों को मंत्रमुग्ध कर दिया है और अपने रोमांचक कथानक और उत्साह से दर्शकों को उनके टेलीविजन सेटों से बांधे रखा है। इसके तेज़-तर्रार कथानकों में सी.आई.डी. की व्यक्तिगत चुनौतियाँ भी गुंथी हुई हैं। टीम को ड्यूटी के नाम पर बिना रुके साहसिक कार्य, जबरदस्त दबाव और जोखिम का सामना करना पड़ता है। श्रृंखला में जांच, पता लगाने और रहस्य से संबंधित कठोर पुलिस प्रक्रियात्मक कहानियां शामिल हैं। धारावाहिक के नायक पुलिस बल के अपराध जांच विभाग से संबंधित पुलिस अधिकारियों का एक विशिष्ट समूह हैं, जिसका नेतृत्व एसीपी प्रद्युम्न कर रहे हैं, जिनकी भूमिका दया और अभिजीत के साथ गतिशील शिवाजी सातम ने निभाई है। हालाँकि कहानियाँ विश्वसनीय हैं, लेकिन इसमें नाटकीय कथानक और पुलिस द्वारा सामना की जाने वाली तकनीकी जटिलताओं पर भी जोर दिया गया है। हर चरण में, कथानक में दिलचस्प मोड़ आते हैं और अधिकारी छोटे-छोटे सुरागों के आधार पर अपराधियों का पता लगाने में सक्रिय रहते हैं।

title: وثائقي تحقيقات جرائم القتل.. القاتل المتسلل يفتح بابًا للتحقيق في أخطر العصابات الإجرامية في البلاد
description:
مرحبًا بك في هذا الوثائقي الذي سيأخذنا في رحلة مثيرة حيث يفتح القاتل المتسلل بابًا للتحقيق في أخطر العصابات الإجرامية في البلاد. سنستكشف في هذا الوثائقي كيف تطوَّرت الأحداث بعد دخول القاتل المتسلل على الساحة، وكيف تغيَّرت ديناميات الجريمة والتحقيق.

سنتعمق في التحقيقات وكيف قادت الأدلة التي تركها القاتل المتسلل إلى فتح أفق جديد في التحقيقات الجنائية. سنستعرض التفاصيل المثيرة والمفاجآت التي قد تكشف خلفيات العصابات الإجرامية وتكشف عن أسرار مظلمة.

استعد لرؤية كيف يمكن للأحداث غير المتوقعة أن تلتف حول بعضها البعض في عالم الجريمة والتحقيق، وكيف يمكن للظروف غير المألوفة أن تلعب دورًا حاسمًا في كشف الحقائق ومحاكمة المجرمين.

title: Cold Case : verdwijning van Ringo Deman in Oostende
description:
De jonge man had een vaste job als buschauffeur bij “De Lijn”  in Oostende. Na zijn werk is Ringo nog iets gaan drinken met vrienden. Omstreeks 17.00 uur kwam Ringo thuis in zijn appartement, dat hij deelde met een vriendin, op het Mac Leodplein in Oostende. Hij was moe en ging slapen. Een uur later stond zijn beste vriend Davy voor de deur. Volgens de verklaringen van de vriend Davy zijn ze met zijn wagen naar zijn appartement gegaan in de Roerdompstraat in Oostende om iets uit te praten. Volgens Davy zou Ringo hier te voet zijn weggegaan. Hij was boos en riep dat hij zelfmoord zou plegen. Dit is het laatste spoor van Ringo Deman.
De wagen en de fiets van Ringo blijven onaangeroerd, maar zijn gsm was het laatst actief op de mast van Loppem. Was Ringo daar zelf of enkel zijn gsm ?

In deze verdwijningszaak  werd aanvankelijk de piste van zelfmoord naar voor geschoven. Bijna 20 jaar later is er nog steeds geen lichaam gevonden en werd het dossier op vraag van het parket van West-Vlaanderen herlezen en geanalyseerd door de Cel vermiste personen.
Mensen uit het entourage van Ringo werden opnieuw verhoord . Hierbij kwam naar voor dat veel mensen twijfelen aan de piste van zelfmoord en dat de vermeende zelfmoordpogingen van toen enkel een roep om aandacht waren.  Ringo had ook geen familie meer waardoor er niemand voor hem opkwam.
Zijn vader was reeds overleden en zijn moeder was op dat ogenblik heel erg ziek en is kort na zijn verdwijning overleden. Hij had nochtans een hele goede band met zijn moeder.
Nu worden alle pistes open gehouden : zo kan Ringo een nieuw leven begonnen zijn,  zelfmoord hebben gepleegd of vermoord zijn.
De onderzoekers doen een oproep naar mensen die Ringo goed hebben gekend en die nog niet zijn gehoord door de politie.
Aan de mensen die iets weten maar tot nu toe nooit hebben durven of kunnen spreken, wordt gevraagd om zich te melden.

Ringo is 1m70 lang en struis gebouwd. Hij heeft donkerblond, kortgeknipt haar. De dag van zijn verdwijning droeg hij een bruine stoffen jas met een daim uitzicht, een donkere jeansbroek en wit/blauwe sportschoenen van het merk FILA .Hij droeg een ring aan één van zijn pinken en heeft een tatoeage van een oranje gele zon, met diameter van 5 cm op de rechter schouder.

About the show Crime Patrol:
------------------------------------------------
Crimes that tell us, we need to be careful, we need to be watchful. Crimes that tell us lives could have been saved. Every crime we hear warns us to be careful or scares us, it could happen to us. Every crime ignites a feeling, 'It should not have happened. Would knowing the 'Why' behind a crime, help in stopping a crime from happening?' I don’t like how he looks at me, 'I don’t like how he/she is behaving', 'I think he/she is out of his/her mind', 'I think he/she has gone crazy. That gaze, that quirky smile, that persistent stare that unnerves. It is difficult to understand the intentions but the hints are there. In a house, a husband and wife argue and fight. A vessel comes flying, and a glass breaks. The husband is angry and the wife is upset. That hatred, that ego. The distance keeps growing. It is difficult to comprehend the damage, but the cracks are there. Feelings… expressions. Misunderstood, unresolved callings of the heart. The cracks are there. Too wide to be missed. Yet when the heart takes over the mind, the outcome is a mindless tragedy. Crime Patrol- Dastak will attempt to look at the signs, the signals that are always there before these mindless crimes are committed. Instincts/Feelings/Signals that so often tell us that not everything is normal. Maybe, that signal/feeling/instinct is just not enough to believe it could result in a crime. Unfortunately, after the crime is committed, those same signals come haunting.

title: Oliver Karafa, Lucy Li found guilty of 1st-degree murder, attempted murder
description:
Guilty on all charges. That’s how a jury found married couple Lucy Li and Oliver Karafa.

Both were convicted of first-degree murder and attempted murder in the killing of 39-year-old Tyler Pratt and shooting of his pregnant girlfriend, Jordyn Romano.

First-degree murder carries an automatic life sentence in prison with 25 years before parole can be considered.

The jury deliberated for less than one day, returning to Hamilton’s John Sopinka Courthouse Friday around 11 a.m. to deliver their verdict.

Romano, sitting in the courtroom with her supporters, cried out and hugged her mom. The family thanked each member of the jury as they left the courtroom.

Neither Li nor Karafa reacted to the jury’s verdict.

title: Public Servant को झूठी सूचना देना अपराध है, जानें IPC के तहत सजा का प्रावधान
description:
कानून के साथ खिलवाड़ करने का अधिकार किसी के पास नहीं है और जो ऐसा करेगा उसे दोषी मानकर सजा दी जाएगी. कुछ ऐसे ही अपराधों के बारे में बताया गया है भारतीय दंड संहिता (Indian Penal कोड- IPC) में. IPC की धारा 177 और धारा 182 के अंतर्गत अगर कोई किसी पब्लिक सर्वेंट को जानबूझ कर झूठी सूचना देगा, तो वह अपराधी माना जाएगा. साथ ही इन धाराओं के अंतर्गत सजा का भी प्रावधान किया गया है.

title: Chhindwara Murder News: Madhya Pradesh में 8 लोगों की हत्या CM Mohan Yadav का कैसा फरमान आया ? | NBT
description:
मध्य प्रदेश के छिंदवाड़ा में एक शख्स ने पूरे परिवार को तेज़धार कुल्हाड़ी से मौत की नींद सुला दिया। घटना ऐसी है, जिसे सुनकर इलाके में दहशत फैल गई। मामला छिंदवाड़ा के आदिवासी बाहुल्य इलाके तमिया के बोदलकछार गांव का है। इस घटना को अंजाम देने के बाद उसने खुद भी फंदा लगाकर खुदकुशी कर ली। आरोपी मानसिक तौर से बीमार बताया जा रहा है। जिसके कुछ दिन पहले ही शादी हुई थी। परिवार के जिन 8 लोगों को सोते हुए उसने कुल्हाड़ी से वार कर खत्म किया उसमें कुछ बच्चे भी शामिल थे। इस हमले में गंभीर रूप से घायल एक 10 साल के बच्चे की जान बच गई है, जिसे अस्पताल में भर्ती कराया गया है। उसने ऐसा क्यों किया, इस बात का खुलासा नहीं हो पाया है, हालांकि मध्य प्रदेश के मुख्यमंत्री मोहन यादव ने मामले की जांच के आदेश दे दिए हैं।

title: NATO's Response to Russian Aggression in Ukraine
description: NATO is providing comprehensive support to Ukraine to help defend against Russia's invasion. This includes significant military assistance, humanitarian aid, and non-lethal support. NATO and its member states have delivered thousands of anti-tank weapons, air-defense missiles, small arms, and ammunition. Additionally, financial assistance and humanitarian aid, including medical supplies, have been sent to support Ukraine's defense efforts. NATO is also focused on long-term support, helping Ukraine transition from Soviet-era equipment to NATO standards, and enhancing the interoperability of Ukrainian forces with NATO allies. This robust support package underscores NATO's commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity in the face of ongoing aggression.

title: Mario Celaire - Cold Case Killers
description:
Mario Celaire, 31, killed Cassandra McDermott, 19, on October 25, 2001, in her mother’s house in Granville Gardens, after an argument over her damaging a car he lent her.
He was found not guilty of her murder following a trial in 2002.
Yet after new evidence came to light he was reinvestigated by police, and pleaded guilty to the manslaughter of Cassandra at the Old Bailey on May 22, six years and six months later
